{{champion:266}} He's got severe identity issues. Clearly the worst pick of his class though, imo. His passive revive and sustain eats up the entirety of his power budget leaving him in a very unstable state. 

I think he should be switched into a more skill-based, skill reliant champion like {{champion:114}} or {{champion:92}} or {{champion:62}} ; instead of competing for the attack speed-oriented auto-attacking fighter role which is already over-populated: {{champion:106}} {{champion:5}} {{champion:23}} {{champion:48}} {{champion:19}} {{champion:56}} {{champion:2}} {{champion:24}} {{champion:10}} {{champion:11}} {{champion:77}} {{champion:39}} 

People say there are too many complex champions... I wholeheartedly disagree. There are so many of these fighter champions i described above that their latest one {{champion:266}}, suffers from a severe lack of originality and identity.
